I will never forget the day sir Pathak kicked my group out of the class for making a HK pot as a science project 😂 I had even made a whole big speech about thermodynamics and how the HK Pot works,sadly we had all our parents called however I was still given a chance to explain my project for which they gave us all just passing marks cause my presentation was on point cause I really knew how a HK pot works. Till date I make the best HK cause I actually studied the science of it in regards to what kinda flavour what kind of coal the temperature of the water everything! I really believe making HK is an art.

Made this in himachal, It was very cold.🥶
One of the most difficult reels I had to Flim cause I made all the 3 parts in one go. It was super cold and I wasn't even able to say my lines. This took me 3 hours and now I am terribly sick however I felt like I made something cool after a long time so that makes me really happy. Also it rained once in between.
Some random guys from Delhi saw me there and really judged me for my wig and attire, I don't blame them cause even if I saw shivani (My female character) in the forest I would freak out too. 
I thought I was high up in the mountains and who would even come there? But apparently Delhi people can reach anywhere. Luckily one of them recognized me and told the rest who I was and then it got less awkward 😭

I'm sorry I haven't posted in a while in all honesty I genuinely lost interest in creating content. I had Alot of things going on in my personal life which made me really unhappy and its pretty difficult to write comedy content when you're sad. I also just felt like whatever I was writing or putting out there was just not good enough. As creators we are extremely insecure especially I am. I start to compare myself Alot to other creators and tend to scrap Alot of ideas thinking that they are not really good enough. But recently I asked myself what is it that I enjoyed the most when writing content and it was writing about Sufiyan. I love this character so so much. I realise I started treating IG like my job which is true that it is actually how I make money but I remember when I started out it was purely for Making things that I thought was funny. So I guess for now I'm just gonna stick to the basics and create content that makes me happy. 
I would like to thank my friends @cant.geet.enough and @simrxns for always reminding about how good I am and that it is not the end of the world. 
I know looking at my content y'all might never assume all this about me but trust me I'm just a kid trying to make sense of this world through his humour. Nusta paisa Nusta paisa 💵
#kevinzingkhai
